{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"cbd330fb-03f4-4c27-9fb5-ecfef95f5c79","content":"The issue is the **file compilation order** in the `.fsproj`. In F#, files can only reference types from files listed **above** them. Currently `Services.fs` is listed before `Domain.fs`, but `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`.","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_2mP2vaVy7iBBSGO1D95ncn","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Fixing F# file order"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"tooluse_rODsR6fy9HGYwsz75hvhPI","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-d0b7030dd4ba495ca36c33b654f85d56/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />","new_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-d0b7030dd4ba495ca36c33b654f85d56/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"861643df-9f9f-418d-81ac-fd8206e18df4","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file order matters — files can only reference modules/types defined in files that appear **earlier** in the compilation order. The `.fsproj` lists:\n\n1. `Services.fs` — opens `BrokenOrder.Domain`, but `Domain.fs` hasn't been compiled yet\n2. `Domain.fs` — defines the types\n3. `Program.fs` — uses both\n\nThe fix is to put `Domain.fs` before `Services.fs`.","outputTokens":399,"requestId":"0407:4010A:423198:4D7D8E:69F00425"},"id":"9c9fb8e5-c290-46ef-ab2e-1e701174e886","timestamp":"2026-04-28T00:49:49.006Z","parentId":"6035e70f-20b4-404c-b036-cb90d74b8735"}
